items.name: deepface-emotion
items.description: DeepFace Emotion Detection is a Python project that recognizes human emotions in real-time using a webcam. It leverages DeepFace and TensorFlow for accurate facial analysis. OpenCV is used to capture video frames and display detected emotions. The system can identify emotions like happy, sad, angry, surprised, and neutral.

items.name: Design-and-Synthesis-of-a-4-Bit-Priority-Encoder-using-Verilog-HDL-in-Synopsys-Workshop
items.description: A 4-bit Priority Encoder is a combinational circuit that converts four inputs (D3–D0) into a 2-bit output based on priority. D3 has the highest priority. A valid signal indicates active input. The design is implemented in Verilog HDL and synthesized using Synopsys Workshop.
